IV) The five-year accident history:



On December 20, 2016 two Instrument technicians were calibrating a level transmitter on top of an ammonia storage tank. One of the technicians opened the calibration chamber to verify the level float was all the way up. Ammonia vapor was released from the chamber and the technician was exposed to some of the vapor. The technicians reported the incident to the control room and Operations immediately began the process to close the isolation valves. The technician exposed to the ammonia vapor was transported by emergency services to an area hospital for evaluation and treatment. Required agency notifications were made for the release which was calculated to be 917 pounds of ammonia vapor.  There were no off-site impacts.



